  "_README": [
    "Overlay file mapping topic-index → display names for Geriatrics and InternalMedicine.",
    "Mishpacha is NOT in this file — its data/topics.json already has {en, he} fields.",
    "",
    "Why this exists (and not directly in PWA repos):",
    "  Geri/Pnimit data/topics.json is consumed by runtime code, build scripts, and tests as",
    "  raw keyword-stem arrays. Changing the schema in those repos would cascade through",
    "  src/core/data-loader.js, multiple test files, Python tooling, etc.",
    "",
    "  This overlay is read by refresh_syllabus_data.py and merged into syllabus_data.json,",
    "  giving every downstream consumer (study plan generator, in-app Phase 2 feature) clean",
    "  display names without touching the PWA repos at all.",
    "",
    "  When/if the PWA repos eventually adopt {en, he} natively, this file can be deleted",
    "  and refresh_syllabus_data.py simplified.",
    "",
    "Indices map to position in each repo's data/topics.json — DO NOT reorder.",
    "If new topics are added to a repo, append entries here at the matching index."
